# Line endings are byte-significant for mcpact governed-server packs.
#
# `mcpact.lock` records the SHA-256 of every generated file, and taudit-mcp
# embeds `.mcpact/source.mcpact.toml` + `.mcpact/mcpact.lock` via include_str!
# and re-checks those digests at serve time
# (crates/taudit-mcp/src/server_config.rs::verify_pack_integrity). A CRLF
# checkout changes the embedded bytes, so the recomputed digest no longer
# matches the lock that was generated over the committed LF content and the MCP
# server refuses to start. Pin every file class an mcpact pack can cover to LF
# on all platforms — Windows core.autocrlf must not reintroduce CRLF.
*.rs    text eol=lf
*.toml  text eol=lf
*.json  text eol=lf
*.md    text eol=lf
*.lock  text eol=lf
